**Simple Login Form in HTML**
================================

Below is a simple HTML page with a login form consisting of email and password fields, along with a submit button.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Login Form</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: lightgray;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }

        form {
            width: 30%;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid gray;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background-color: white;
        }

        label {
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .error {
            color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <form action="" method="post">
        <label for="email">Email</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>

        <label for="password">Password</label>
        <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>

        <button type="submit">Login</button>
    </form>
</body>
</html>
```

This HTML code will create a basic login form with the following features:

*   The form will be centered on the webpage, with a light gray background and a white form container.
*   The form will have an email input field and a password input field, both with a label for clarity.
*   There will be a submit button that will trigger the form submission.
*   The form will be enclosed in a container element with a style applied to it for a cleaner and more visually appealing design.
